# M6 P01 audit — gravity free-fall test.
#
# Pre-fix (Phase 5 bug): pose_write_to_particles set prev=pos every
# tick, zeroing Verlet velocity. Gravity acted like terminal velocity
# of ~80 px/sec (linear) instead of accelerating g = 2400 px/s². Drop
# from 100 px above floor was a slow drift instead of an impact.
#
# Post-fix: pose_write_to_particles uses kinematic translate (move pos
# AND prev by the same delta), preserving velocity. Gravity
# accelerates as expected.
#
# Manual visual check: at t=30 (0.5 s) the mech should have fallen
# ~300 px (s = 0.5 * 2400 * 0.5² = 300). At t=60 (1 s) it should be on
# the floor (started at 200 px above, fell 1200 px capped by floor).

window 1280 720
seed   77 33
out    build/shots/m6_fall_test

loadout Trooper "Pulse Rifle" Sidearm Light Standard
spawn_at 640 480
mouse    1100 360

at  5 shot t005_drop_start
at 15 shot t015_quarter_sec
at 30 shot t030_half_sec
at 45 shot t045_three_quarter
at 60 shot t060_one_sec
at 90 shot t090_settled
at 120 shot t120_settled
contact_sheet fall_sheet cols 4
at 121 end
